  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to the Migrant Learners&apos; Unit to Improve the Inclusion of Migrant Learners Within Mainstream Education in Malta</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to provide technical support to the Migrant Learners Unit (MLU) of the Ministry of Education and Employment (MEDE) to improve the inclusion of migrant learners within mainstream education in Malta. It is expected that the project will enhance migrant learners&apos; participation in lifelong learning so that they become active members of society. The project, thus, will contribute to improving the quality of education provision, including by supporting migrant learners&apos; inclusion and facilitating more effective and collaborative synergies between educational and other stakeholders (e.g. parents, civil society, local councils, local communities at large, non-governmental and international organizations). Overall, the project will contribute to fostering school cultures and environments that acknowledge, celebrate and develop the potential of all learners, while strengthening collaborative systems to support migrant learners&apos; inclusion to enhance a &apos;sense of belonging&apos; and social cohesion.</narrative>
  </description>
